On November 15th, President Joe Biden signed the Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act into law. Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a speech to commemorate the historic day, thanking President Biden for his leadership and highlighting the importance of the bill. She emphasized that the infrastructure plan will create millions of good-paying, union jobs for Americans and improve the nation's competitiveness. Harris also mentioned that the bill is part one of two, with the second part being the Build Back Better Act, which aims to lower costs, cut taxes for working families, and address the climate crisis. She concluded by urging everyone to continue believing in the potential of the American people and the country.